descript.abstract: This theme shows line representation of the jurisdictional and cartographic county perimeters for Oregon. This depiction of the boundaries as recorded in Oregon Revised Statutes may not match county plat records due to source records. Coordinates derived from this position should be used for general location and cartographic representation only. Survey monuments on the ground are definitive location markers.
descript.supplinf: BLM (Bureau of Land Management), CFF (Cartographic Feature File), DLG (Digital Line Graph), DRG (Digital Raster Graphic), FIPS (Federal Information Processing Standard), GCD (Geographic Coordinate Database layer), GCDB (Geographic Coordinate Data Base), HYD (WODDB Hydrologic Features layer), LLI (Landlines layer), USFS (U.S. Forest Service), USGS (U.S. Geological Survey), WODDB (Western Oregon Digital Data Base)

idinfo.accconst: Discretionary, contains no sensitive information - generally considered releasable.
idinfo.useconst: None; however, users are reminded that the legal descriptions for County boundaries are published in the Oregon Revised Statutes (ORS 201.010 - 201.370) and the Revised Code for Washington (RCW 36.04.010 - 36.04.400). Any surveys of the county boundaries will be recorded in the counties, and with the Department of Natural Resources Public Land Survey Office in Washington.

procstep.procdesc: BLM used the cited sources (see source information) to extract the desired line work based on Oregon and Washington Statutes.
Corrected points along Oregon/Washington border and changed source of the Snake River for boundaries along Idaho.
Replaced all features with defining feature of SUBDIVISION with recalculated PLSS data. Replaced Canada border features to match published coordinates from the International Boundary Commission.
Replaced portion of Washington/Multnomah border to incorporate annex of "Area 93" by Washington County.
